content.description: Start on two solid finger buckets. Find your feet and go big for a rail. Then follow decent holds to a slopey and slightly heady top out. May be easier for taller people.
content.location: First line to the right of the bleach blonde slab. To the left of Green Shell.

content.description: A gem.  The obvious line up the center of the tall, stunning and intimidating slab.  No contrivances, just climb it, and don’t exit left.Probably climbed many times before.One of the best and most intimidating climbs in the park.
content.location: If at the playground.. hidden back and right (north) in a corridor on the other side of the rock formation.

content.description: Amazing slab climbing.  Climb up left side of slab using cool slopey features and an up close and personal pod.
content.location: This problem is located in another corridor on the far side of the large rock group.

content.description: Climb much harder slab route just right of Near Sighted Gynecologist.
Start on a jug, pull up through some crimps and underclings. Keep it together for the slopey top out.
content.location: To the right of the slab problems.

content.description: Squat start on two solid side pulls. Move up through incut side pulls and jugs to a slopey top out.
Sit/squat start on a rail. Find a nice undercling then stand into a big reach to a jug. Follow good holds up to the top out.
Sit start, move up and work your way upwards to the left to top out. Due to it's location this one takes longer to dry, please be mindful.
content.protection: Can fit a smaller pad near the start. The rest is too tight to protect. Falling on the top out would not be good.
content.location: Located in the corridor to the left of the slab. this can be seen straight ahead as you enter the slab area.

content.description: Go up the right side of the face using the crack and left hand side pulls
content.location: The right route on the rock across from the slab.

content.description: This route is tall. Unfortunately tall doesn't always mean amazing quality. Pull one or two slightly difficult moves then cruise jugs for the top. Or start right and traverse left on ledge feet to decrease the difficulty.
content.location: The tall rock opposite the slab problems

content.description: Another tucked away area with a handful of problems. The slab is tall and has excellent movement, a must do for the area. This section of the park tends to take the longest to dry, sometimes requiring up to an extra day compared to the rest of the rock. Please be mindful when checking out conditions here.
